  "prompt": "How many books does an average person read in a year?",
  "response": "The number of books read by an average person in a year can vary significantly based on factors such as age, educational background, personal interests, and cultural context. However, broad statistics provide some general insights:\n\n- In the United States and the UK, surveys often indicate that the average person reads around 12 books per year.\n- In other countries, the number can vary. For example, readers in some European countries like Germany or France might read fewer or more books annually.\n\nThese numbers are averages and can vary significantly from person to person. Some individuals might read many more books, while others might read very few or none at all.",
